author: Eliza Collins
title: Donald Trump getting ready his Hillary Clinton impression for 'SNL'
text:
Donald Trump is excited to host “Saturday Night Live” on Nov. 7, and there very well might be an impression of Democratic front-runner Hillary Clinton in his future. Trump, who was speaking to MNBC’s Katy Tur on Wednesday, said he would “certainly” do his best Hillary on SNL.
Clinton appeared on SNL earlier this month and whipped out a Trump impression — she’s also been known to offer it up on the campaign trail.
But there's one candidate Trump will resist doing an impression of: Republican rival Jeb Bush.
“I was gonna fall asleep in the chair, but I’m not gonna do that,” a milder-seeming Trump said to Tur. He has traded jabs with Bush on the trail, often calling him "low energy. "
